The film is about 
Sasha, a young Eastern European girl leaves her newly deceased sugar daddy, finding refuge in the quirky, diverse friendships of Los Angeles. Her departure from her newly deceased sugar daddy and the shadows of her former life offers her a fresh start. But when the emotional scars she buried come to the surface, she must confront the trauma she thought she’d left behind—just as the rain she’s avoided begins to fall, both literally and metaphorically, in the city of endless sun.
